1 (b) declaratory relief;
2 (c) compensatory damages;
3 (d) punitive damages;
4 (e) statutory damages, which are the following amounts:
5 (i) $100,000 for a strict violation of [section 2];
6 (ii) $1,000,000 for a violation of [section 2] that is committed negligently or recklessly; or
7 (iii) no less than $5,000,000 for a violation of [section 2] that is committed purposely or knowingly;
8 and
9 (f) reasonable attorney fees and costs incurred in bringing the action.
10 (2) In addition to the remedies provided in subsection (1), a victim may seek restitution.
11 (3) For each unique violation under [section 2], a plaintiff's recovery of statutory damages is limited
12 to one subsection under subsection (1)(e)(i) through (1)(e)(iii).
13 (4) In an action in which the remedies under subsection (1) are ordered:
14 (a) compensatory damages for each violation must be paid to the victim;
15 (b) the amount of punitive and statutory damages must be apportioned for each violation as
16 follows:
17 (i) 50% to a victim, or equally divided among multiple victims, if reasonably identified by the court
18 regardless of the victim's involvement as a plaintiff;
19 (ii) 30% to a private plaintiff or, if there is no private plaintiff, to a victim, or equally divided among
20 multiple victims, if reasonably identified by the court regardless of the victim's involvement as a plaintiff;
21 (iii) the remaining amount to the department to be deposited into a state special revenue account
22 to the credit of the department; and
23 (c) attorney fees and costs shall be paid to the party who incurred the fees and costs.
24
25 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Codification instruction. [Sections 1 through 4] are intended to be
26 codified as a new part of a new chapter of Title 30, and the provisions of Title 30 apply to [sections 1 through 4].
27
